      "type": "service",
      "title": "Bare surface composite (SCMap)",
      "description": "SCMaP is a specialised processing chain for detecting and analysing spectra of bare soils/surfaces. Bare surface and soil pixels are selected using a combined NDVI and NBR index (PVIR2) that optimises the exclusion of photosynthetically active and non-active vegetation. The index is calculated and applied for each individual pixel combined with a regional threshold map. The result is described in here: https://download.geoservice.dlr.de/SOILSUITE/files/EUROPE_5Y/000_Data_Overview/SoilSuite_Data_Description_Europe_V1.pdf",
      "cost_estimate": 0.2,
